{{Infobox officeholder | name = Abdul Nasser El Hakim | native_name = عبد الناصر الحكيم | native_name_lang = ara | image = Nasser Hakim.jpg | imagesize = 220 | office = Minister of Economic Affairs | monarch = [[Willem-Alexander of the Netherlands]] | governor = [[Lucille George-Wout]] | term_start = 10 October 2010 | term_end =29 September 2012 | predecessor = office created | successor = [[José Jardim]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|11|1}} | birth_place = Beirut, Lebanon | party = [[Movementu Futuro Kòrsou]] | website = }}
'''Abdul Nasser El Hakim''' ({{lang-ar|عبد الناصر الحكيم}}; born November 1, 1960) is a Lebanese-born [[Curaçao]]an businessman and politician. He was the first Minister of Economic Development of Curaçao following the [[dissolution of the Netherlands Antilles]] in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thenational.ae/thenationalconversation/industry-insights/technology/down-to-earth-island-nation-plans-a-rocketing-space-flight-venture |title=Down to earth island nation plans a rocketing space-flight venture |work=The National |date=April 17, 2012 |author=Hunter, Gregor |accessdate=April 18, 2012}}</ref> He was one of the founding members of the political party [[Movementu Futuro Kòrsou|MFK]]{{Citation needed|date=October 2012}}.
==Early life== Abdul Nasser El Hakim was born on November 1, 1964, in [[Beirut]], Lebanon and migrated from Lebanon in 1985 to Curaçao.{{Citation needed|date= May 2018}}
==Businessman== In 1990, El Hakim started his business Optika Hakim and has led the company to grow into the largest optical chain on Curaçao, while also starting several other companies. He was Regional Latin American UNDP Goodwill Ambassador and also translated the [[Quran]] into [[Papiamentu]].<ref>http://www.onislam.net/english/news/3338/435702</ref>
==Social and cultural organizations== El Hakim is president of Hakim Foundation, president of World Lebanese Cultural Union-Dutch Caribbean, Chairman of Miss Lebanon Committee, Regional Goodwill Ambassador-Latin America<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.livelebanon.net/GoodwillAmbassadors.aspx |title=Goodwill Ambassadors |work=UNDP |year=2011 |author=UNDP |accessdate=2 October 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225171135/http://www.livelebanon.net/GoodwillAmbassadors.aspx|archivedate=25 February 2013}}{{failed verification|date=October 2016|reason=name does not appear in archive or current equivalent http://www.lb.undp.org/content/lebanon/en/home/ourwork/national_goodwillambassadors.html}}</ref> and Founding Member of Movementu Futuro Korsow (Political Party).{{Citation needed|date= May 2018}}
==Business related non-profit organizations== El Hakim is Vice-President- Latin America (2005) to the Lebanese International Business Council, President to the Caribbean Business Council and President to the Federation of Arab-Latin Chambers of Commerce.{{Citation needed|date= May 2018}}
